results.wikipedia_summary: Chachalacas are mainly brown birds from the genus Ortalis. These cholis are found in wooded habitats in far southern United States (Texas), Mexico, and Central and South America. They are social, can be very noisy and often remain fairly common even near humans, as their relatively small size makes them less desirable to hunters than their larger relatives.
